
Function: ADD1

Syntax:   (ADD1 num1)
    or:   (1+ num1)

 num1 (required, evaluated) - a number.

Returns:

 The sum of the argument and 1 (num1 + 1), of the same type as num1.

Processing:

 (ADD1 n) is equivalent to (+ n 1)

 See member $ARITH for more information.

Errors signaled:

 See member $ARITH for more information.

Notes:

 See member $ARITH for more information.

Examples:

 (ADD1 2)              ==> 3
 (ADD1 2147483647)     ==> 21
 (ADD1 -1000000000000) ==> -9999
 (1+ 1.0)              ==> 2.0
 (1+ 3.5F0)            ==> 4.5F0

